## 🚀 Running the Services

### Method 1: Run All Services (Recommended)

#### Terminal 1: Next.js App
```bash
cd /home/z/my-project
bun run dev
```
**Runs on:** Port 3000

#### Terminal 2: WebSocket Service
```bash
cd /home/z/my-project/mini-services/websocket-service
bun run dev
```
**Runs on:** Port 3002

#### Terminal 3: YOLOv8 Detection
```bash
cd /home/z/my-project/mini-services/yolo-detection
source venv/bin/activate  # Linux/macOS
# or venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
python3 detection.py
```

---

### Method 2: Background Services (Production)

#### Create Start Script

Create `/home/z/my-project/start-services.sh`:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

echo "Starting Canteen Monitor Services..."

# Kill existing processes
pkill -f "bun run dev"
pkill -f "node.*index.js"
pkill -f "python3.*detection.py"

# Start Next.js
echo "Starting Next.js..."
cd /home/z/my-project
nohup bun run dev > nextjs.log 2>&1 &
echo "Next.js started on port 3000"

# Start WebSocket
echo "Starting WebSocket service..."
cd /home/z/my-project/mini-services/websocket-service
nohup bun run dev > websocket.log 2>&1 &
echo "WebSocket started on port 3002"

# Start YOLOv8
echo "Starting YOLOv8 detection..."
cd /home/z/my-project/mini-services/yolo-detection
source venv/bin/activate
nohup python3 detection.py > detection.log 2>&1 &
echo "YOLOv8 detection started"

echo "All services started!"
echo "Check logs:"
echo "  Next.js:    tail -f /home/z/my-project/nextjs.log"
echo "  WebSocket:  tail -f /home/z/my-project/mini-services/websocket-service/websocket.log"
echo "  Detection:  tail -f /home/z/my-project/mini-services/yolo-detection/detection.log"
```

#### Make it executable and run
```bash
chmod +x /home/z/my-project/start-services.sh
/home/z/my-project/start-services.sh
```

